The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Thursday, February 03, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Behrampore, Feb. 2: Moloy Shankar Aich, an officer of the jails and social welfare department, was caught accepting a bribe by the subdivisional officer of Behrampore and handed over to police. Aich is a probation officer of the jails department in Murshidabad.

 He was allegedly receiving Rs 2,000 from the father of a Class IX student lodged in a juvenile home to prepare an investigation report in his favour. The student is accused of stealing blank answer-scripts distributed by the Madhyamik board. 

 Krishnagar: Pradeep Das, 35, was killed and another youth, Tarun Pal, was injured when criminals they were chasing opened fire at Gobrapota village in Nadia. Alerted by screams from the house of an oil mill owner, the two went after a group of about 20 miscreants who robbed the businessman?s house. 

 Krishnagar: A quack and his two brothers were arrested from Dharmanarayanpur village in Nadia?s Nakashipara when the quack?s 22-year-old wife complained that they had forcibly carried out three abortions on her during their four years of marriage. He apparently was keen on another marriage and so did not want children. 

 Calcutta: A middle-aged medical practitioner, Deepak Roy, was arrested from Kasba after he failed to produce medical degrees. Equipment for making medicines was seized from his house.




